From 4e4f9915166c772ff3076700c02f6289a1fffbc6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Valerio Bozzolan <nsa+gitspam@succhia.cz>
Date: Tue, 24 Feb 2026 11:32:43 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 40/50] arc browse: avoid unneeded question 'Which URI do you
 want to open?'

Summary:
When the command 'arc browse COMMIT' is executed to
browse a specific commit on your browser web, then
the result now opens immediately, instead of showing
a nonsense question 'Which URI do you want to open?'
(`AMBIGUOUS  Argument "abcdef1234567890" is ambiguous.`)
and showing you two equivalent URIs.

Closes T16410

Test Plan:
Enter in phorge/ and open the initial Phorge commit in various ways:

    arc browse 081689d61a4e2601031e5f40ebec0c94f3a9ed90
    arc browse rP081689d61a4e2601031e5f40ebec0c94f3a9ed90

The page opens immediately here:

    https://we.phorge.it/rP081689d61a4e2601031e5f40ebec0c94f3a9ed90

No silly questions anymore.

Enter in arcanist/ and run the same. It also works there.

Enter in arcanist/ and try other things, like:

    arc browse README.md
    arc browse ./README.md
    arc browse ./src/../README.md
    arc browse --branch master README.md

They all open the README to this link. No regressions.

    https://we.phorge.it/source/arcanist/browse/master/README.md

Try also this:

    arc browse --branch stable README.md

It opens here. No regressions.

    https://we.phorge.it/source/arcanist/browse/stable/README.md

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, aklapper, avivey

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, avivey

